  "time_ut": 1661053554,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dca 08\u0d9a \u0db4\u0dd0\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2  \u0db4\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd4\u0db9\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dab\u0dba \u0db6\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0da7\u0db8 \u0db6\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The amount of fallow fields in 08 districts will be reduced to zero",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sri Lanka currently has about 100,000 acres of uncultivated fallow paddy. Most of them are located in the Western Province. Out of the fallow fields in the island, the amount of paddy fields that can be cultivated is about 50,000 acres and the rest of the fallow fields are in a condition that cannot be cultivated.",
        "For this reason, the Minister of Agriculture, Wildlife and Forest Resources Development, Mr. Mahinda Amaraweera, will instruct the Department of Agricultural Development to implement a replanting program by assigning them to those who do not have rice fields for a period of five years, if the owners do not cultivate all the fallow fields that can be cultivated. received",
        "Accordingly, the Department of Farmers' Development started a special program for the replanting of fallow fields. Arrangements have been made to hand over paddy fields for five years to cultivate uncultivated paddy lands under the Agricultural Development Act.",
        "Accordingly, last week, the Department of Agricultural Development held a review meeting on the progress of the last month, where the Department of Agricultural Development stated that the fallow fields in 08 districts of the island have now been cleared.",
        "Thus the fallow fields have been cleared in the districts of Anuradhapura, Polonnaruwa, Monaragala, Ampara, Hambantota, Batticaloa, Kilinochchi and Trincomalee.",
        "There were 21,200 acres of fallow fields in these 08 districts and necessary steps have been taken to cultivate all of them in the next season.",
        "In the meantime, the minister also advised to look into the possibility of cultivating fallow fields that cannot be cultivated in the Western Province through the Sojan cultivation method, an Indonesian cultivation method. The minister pointed out that vegetable and fruit cultivation can be done in swampy lands as well as fresh water fish cultivation in deep canals around the beds under the Sojan system.",
        "The Minister advised to strengthen the program started by the Honorable President Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe for the food security of Sri Lanka and to take steps to replant every fallow field that can be cultivated and to take steps to eliminate all fallow fields in Sri Lanka by the end of next year. gave",
        "Secretary of the Ministry Rohana Pushpakumara, Commissioner General of the Department of Agricultural Development A. H. M. L. Mr. Abeyratne and a group of officials participated."
      ],
